In [54]:
# Normalizing functions are automatically applied column-wise in dataframes

#this is called "whitening" the data
centered_data = (data-data.mean())

standardized_data = (data-data.mean())/data.std()

#min-max normalizing to [0, 1]
min_max_normalized_data=(data-data.min())/(data.max()-data.min())

display(centered_data.describe().round(2))
display(standardized_data.describe().round(2))
display(min_max_normalized_data.describe().round(2))

PCA derivation¶

In [55]:
rng = np.random.RandomState(1)
X = np.dot(rng.rand(2, 2), rng.randn(2, 200)).T
plt.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1])
plt.axis('equal');
In [59]:
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
pca.fit(X)
components = pd.DataFrame(pca.components_, columns=("pc1", "pc2"), index= ("x", "y"))
components

In [61]:
# principal components are like vector axes
# What would be the equation of the axes?

def draw_vector(v0, v1, ax=None):
    ax = ax or plt.gca()
    arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->',
                    linewidth=2,
                    shrinkA=0, shrinkB=0)
    ax.annotate('', v1, v0, arrowprops=arrowprops)

# plot data
plt.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], alpha=0.2)
for length, vector in zip(pca.explained_variance_, pca.components_):
    v = vector * 3 * np.sqrt(length)
    draw_vector(pca.mean_, pca.mean_ + v)
plt.axis('equal');

In [106]:
good_labels = ["Fully Paid", "Does not meet the credit policy. Status:Fully Paid"]
bad_labels  = ["Default", "Charged Off", "Does not meet the credit policy. Status:Charged Off"]
inactive_good = np.where(loans["loan_status"].isin(good_labels), 1, 0) #loans["loan_status"].values
inactive_bad = np.where(loans["loan_status"].isin(bad_labels), 1, 0)

loans.insert(0, "inactive_good", inactive_good, True) 
loans.insert(0, "inactive_bad", inactive_bad, True)

pd.DataFrame({"good":sum(inactive_good), "bad":sum(inactive_bad), "total":sum(inactive_good) + sum(inactive_bad)},
            index={"0"})
